p: Age-standardised new HIV diagnosis rates attributed to heterosexual contact from 2006 to 2010 were higher than in women born in Oceania (IRR 6.80, 95% CI 4.63–9.98), North-West Europe (IRR 2.10, 95% CI 1.37–3.21) North Africa and the Middle East (IRR 8.28, 95% CI 5.16–13.29), South-East Asia (IRR 15.27, 95% CI 11.72–19.90), the Americas (IRR 4.18, 95% CI 2.04–8.57) and Sub-Saharan Africa (IRR 65.55, 95% CI 51.44–83.53) than in Australian-born women. Rates were not significantly different for women from Southern and Eastern Europe, North-East Asia and Southern and Central Asia compared with those born in Australia.
